# RMS Implementation Map

## 1. Personas and Agents

### Seeded Agents (from `scripts/seed_dpah_tables.py`)

The seed script creates 3 agents (CREATOR, REVIEWER, APPROVER) for **each** of the 2 RMS collections (`rms_timesheet`, `rms_projectplan`), yielding 6 `RMS_*` agents total. Agent names follow the convention `{MODULE}_{COLL_SUFFIX}_{PERSONA}`:

| agent_name | collection_id → collection_name | Persona |
|---|---|---|
| RMS_TIMESHEET_CREATOR | (FK → `rms_timesheet`) | CREATOR |
| RMS_TIMESHEET_REVIEWER | (FK → `rms_timesheet`) | REVIEWER |
| RMS_TIMESHEET_APPROVER | (FK → `rms_timesheet`) | APPROVER |
| RMS_PROJECTPLAN_CREATOR | (FK → `rms_projectplan`) | CREATOR |
| RMS_PROJECTPLAN_REVIEWER | (FK → `rms_projectplan`) | REVIEWER |
| RMS_PROJECTPLAN_APPROVER | (FK → `rms_projectplan`) | APPROVER |

**Code reference**: `seed_agents()` in `seed_dpah_tables.py:145-173` generates all 6 via a double loop over collections × personas.

### Agent Configs (in-memory, `app/workflows/rms_workflow/agents.py`)

Only **3 hardcoded configs** exist, all scoped to the RMS module without collection differentiation:

| name | persona | allowed_tools |
|---|---|---|
| RMS_CREATOR | creator | tool_list_tasks, tool_create_task |
| RMS_REVIEWER | reviewer | tool_list_my_tasks, tool_log_hours, tool_log_bulk_hours |
| RMS_APPROVER | approver | tool_list_pending_approvals, tool_approve_worklog |

Note: The in-memory `AGENT_REGISTRY` is **never imported or used** by the node functions in `nodes.py`. The nodes define tools inline via `@tool` decorators and only reference agent names as string literals for DB prompt lookups.

