## 3. State Machine / Routing in graph.py

### Nodes (6 total)

| Node ID | Function | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `parse_intent` | `parse_intent_node` | Classify user intent via LLM classifier |
| `permission_check` | `permission_check_node` | DB lookup + RBAC permission check |
| `permission_blocked` | `permission_blocked_node` | Deny message (OUT_OF_DOMAIN or no permission) |
| `creator_agent` | `creator_agent_node` | Creator persona agent |
| `reviewer_agent` | `reviewer_agent_node` | Reviewer/Filler persona agent |
| `approver_agent` | `approver_agent_node` | Approver persona agent |

### Edges

```
parse_intent → permission_check (always)
permission_check ──conditional(permission_router)──> {permission_blocked, creator_agent, reviewer_agent, approver_agent}
permission_blocked → END (always)
creator_agent → END (always)
reviewer_agent → END (always)
approver_agent → END (always)
```

### Conditional Edge Router: `permission_router`

- `has_permission == False` → `"permission_blocked"`
- `selected_agent_role == "creator"` → `"creator_agent"`
- `selected_agent_role == "reviewer"` → `"reviewer_agent"`
- `selected_agent_role == "approver"` → `"approver_agent"`
- Default (unknown role) → `"permission_blocked"`

### Checkpointer

**None.** `build_rms_graph()` returns `graph_builder.compile()` with no `.checkpointer` argument. No state persistence across sessions.

