## 7. Intent Classifier Output Shape

### `parse_intent_node` state fields set

| Field | Source | Example Values |
|---|---|---|
| `parsed_intent` | `classification.domain` | `"IN_DOMAIN"` or `"OUT_OF_DOMAIN"` |
| `selected_collection` | `classification.collection` | `"rms_timesheet"`, `"rms_projectplan"`, or `""` |
| `selected_agent_role` | `classification.persona.lower()` | `"creator"`, `"reviewer"`, `"approver"`, or `""` |
| `classifier_confidence` | `classification.confidence` | `"HIGH"`, `"MEDIUM"`, `"LOW"` |
| `append_soft_correction` | `domain == "IN_DOMAIN" and confidence in (MEDIUM, LOW)` | `True` or `False` |

### Valid `selected_collection` values

- `"rms_timesheet"` — logged when LLM classifies the request as targeting timesheet operations
- `"rms_projectplan"` — seeded as a collection, but **not hardcoded in any keyword logic** — the keyword fallback in `intent.py` always returns `"rms_timesheet"` regardless of intent

### Valid `selected_agent_role` values

| Value | Keyword triggers | Default when no keywords match |
|---|---|---|
| `"creator"` | `create task`, `new task`, `assign`, `plan task`, `add task`, `create a task` | — |
| `"reviewer"` | `log hours`, `log time`, `fill timesheet`, `my tasks`, `my entries`, `my timesheet`, `work hours`, `i worked`, `show`, `list`, `details`, `what tasks`, etc. | **Default**: reviewer |
| `"approver"` | `approve`, `reject`, `pending approvals`, `approval queue`, `sign off` | — |

**Fallback behavior** (when LLM classifier fails): `keyword_fallback()` in `intent.py` always returns `collection="rms_timesheet"`. Priority order: APPROVER keywords first, then CREATOR, then FILLER/QUERY, defaulting to reviewer. The classifier supports `rms_projectplan` as a collection value via the LLM, but the keyword fallback path never selects it.

